zy-tmux.xyz","score":4,"flags":1,"comment_count":0,"description":"\u003cp\u003eA tmux session manager in Go. It lists all saved sessions as a tree, but only restores one — its processes and scrollback — when you actually open it, instead of bringing everything back eagerly like resurrect/continuum.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe part I'd most like feedback on is the restore model: what gets re-run is controlled by an allow/denylist matched as regexes over the full command, so servers relaunch but destructive commands don't.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eWorks with tmux 2.9–3.7b, one-line install.\u003c/p\u003e\n","description_plain":"A tmux session manager in Go. It lists all saved sessions as a tree, but only restores one — its processes and scrollback — when you actually open it, instead of bringing everything back eagerly like resurrect/continuum.\r\n\r\nThe part I'd most like feedback on is the restore model: what gets re-run is controlled by an allow/denylist matched as regexes over the full command, so servers relaunch but destructive commands don't.\r\n\r\nWorks with tmux 2.9–3.7b, one-line install.","submitter_user":"alchemmist","user_is_author":true,"tags":["go","release","show","unix"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/z1alry","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/z1alry/lazy_tmux_restore_tmux_sessions_lazily"},{"short_id":"w031bw","created_at":"2026-07-21T10:13:09.729-05:00","title":"An open-source alternative to iCloud and Google Photos","url":"https://github.com/Lynavo/lynavo-drive","score":-1,"flags":2,"comment_count":6,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"Yogthos","user_is_author":false,"tags":["programming","vibecoding","web"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/w031bw","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/w031bw/open_source_alternative_icloud_google"},{"short_id":"cvibea","created_at":"2026-07-21T08:32:43.730-05:00","title":"Low- and Mid-Tier Mobile for the Real World","url":"https://csswizardry.com/2026/07/low-and-mid-tier-mobile